  </section>
  <VideoGallery videoIds={['cascada-roca-closeup','cascada-monumental','canon-puente-panoramica']} lang="en" title="Canyon videos" columns={3} />

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="faq-t">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section__header"><h2 id="faq-t">Questions about the canyon</h2></div>
      <div class="faq-list"><details><summary>Can you go hiking in the canyon?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. There are maintained trails that ascend the canyon walls to the viewpoints. The trails do not require specialized equipment, but hiking boots and basic physical fitness are recommended.</div></details><details><summary>How tall are the canyon walls?</summary><div class="faq-answer">The walls of the Tolantongo Canyon reach up to 800 meters at their highest points. Most of the visited area is at the bottom of the canyon.</div></details><details><summary>Is the canyon dangerous?</summary><div class="faq-answer">The tourist area is maintained and has signage. Dangerous zones are clearly marked. Always respect the signage and stay on the marked trails.</div></details></div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
